HEADWORD: Prelusive
<hw>Pre*lu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Prelude</er>.]</ety> <def>Of the nature of a prelude; introductory;
indicating that something of a like kind is to follow.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Prelusive</xex> drops.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Thomson.</au>
--<wordforms><wf>Pre*lu"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
